.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt TMPL_PARSE 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm tmpl_parse ,
.Nm tmpl_key ,
.Nm tmpl_val
.Nd parse key=value input into a template object
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In tmpl/tmpl.h
.Ft int
.Fn tmpl_parse "struct tmpl *t" "const char *input" "size_t len"
.Ft "const char *"
.Fn tmpl_key "const struct tmpl *t"
.Ft "const char *"
.Fn tmpl_val "const struct tmpl *t"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn tmpl_parse
function parses
.Fa len
bytes of
.Fa input
as a
.Sq key=value
pair, storing the results in
.Fa t .
The first
.Sq =
character in
.Fa input
separates the key from the value; subsequent
.Sq =
characters are included in the value.
Any previously stored key and value are replaced.
.Pp
.Fn tmpl_key
and
.Fn tmpl_val
return the key and value stored in
.Fa t ,
respectively.
The returned pointers are valid until the next call to
.Fn tmpl_parse
on the same object or until the object is released.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Fn tmpl_parse
returns 0 on success or a negative
.Xr errno 2
value on failure.
.Fn tmpl_key
and
.Fn tmpl_val
return
.Dv NULL
if no successful parse has been performed on
.Fa t .
.Sh ERRORS
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EINVAL
.Fa t
or
.Fa input
is
.Dv NULL ,
or
.Fa len
is zero.
.It Bq Er ENOMEM
Memory allocation failed.
.It Bq Er ENOMSG
No
.Sq =
character was found in
.Fa input .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr tmpl_new 3
